** Azure parameters **
      
      Parameters are used to change the values for each deployment.
      
      For example, you have a requirement to install a VM with same specs but the location is different. Instead of creating 2 bicep files we can create a location 
      parameter.
      
      Syntax to create a parameter : param <parameter-name> <parameter-data-type>
      
      <parameter-name> is your custom name for parameter.
      <parameter-data-type> is datatype of the parameter like string,
      
      
      
      How to assign a default vaule to the parameter : param <parameter-name> <parameter-data-type> = <default-value>
      Example : param location string = 'westus'
      
      Same code in JSON looks like below 
       
       {
  "$schema": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2019-04-01/deploymentTemplate.json#",
  "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
  "metadata": {
    "_generator": {
      "name": "bicep",
      "version": "0.9.1.41621",
      "templateHash": "14124952696502777844"
    }
  },
  "parameters": {
    "location": {
      "type": "string",
      "defaultValue": "westus"
    }
  },
  "resources": []
}

    You can use this link to convert your bicep code to JSON code : https://bicepdemo.z22.web.core.windows.net/
    
    
 
      
      
      
      
